.Dd December 2025
.Dt CC 7
.Os Fedora
.Sh NAME
.Nm cc
.Nd Conventional Commits cheat sheet
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm <type> Ns Op (scope) Ns Op ! :
.Ar <description>
.Sh DESCRIPTION
A lightweight convention for commit messages to create a machine-readable history.
.Sh TYPES
.Bl -tag -width "refactor" -compact
.It Ic feat
New feature (SemVer: MINOR)
.It Ic fix
Bug fix (SemVer: PATCH)
.It Ic perf
Performance improvement
.It Ic docs
Documentation only
.It Ic style
Formatting, missing semi-colons, etc.
.It Ic refactor
Code change (neither fix nor feature)
.It Ic build
Build system or dependencies (CMake, etc.)
.It Ic ci
CI configuration (GitHub Actions, etc.)
.It Ic test
Adding or fixing tests
.It Ic chore
Maintenance tasks
.El
.Sh BREAKING CHANGES
Indicated by a
.Ic !
after the type/scope or
.Ic BREAKING CHANGE:
in the footer. Triggers a
.Ic MAJOR
version bump.
.Sh EXAMPLES
.Dl fix(parser): resolve overflow in hex reader
.Dl feat(api)!: remove deprecated endpoints
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Lk https://www.conventionalcommits.org
